ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: No changes to my life or behavior
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Practicing social distancing
Practicing social distancing: If yes, how long have you been doing/did you do this for (days)?

Practicing social distancing: If yes, how long have you been doing/did you do this for (days)? Of these number of days, how many did you end up needing to be physically near people, i.e., you were not able to practice social distancing?
Practicing social distancing: If yes, did you choose to do this yourself or did someone else require you to do so?
Practicing social distancing: If yes, did you do this to protect someone else in your household?
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Isolating or quarantining yourself
Isolating or quarantining yourself: If yes, how long have you been doing this for (days)?
Isolating or quarantining yourself: If yes, how long have you been doing this for (days)? Of these number of days, how many did you end up breaking the isolation or quarantine?
Isolating or quarantining yourself: If yes, did you choose to do this yourself or did someone else require you to do so?
Isolating or quarantining yourself: If yes, did you do this to protect someone in your household?
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Caring for someone at home
Caring for someone at home: If yes, a child/children?
Caring for someone at home: If yes, an elderly person?
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Working from home
Working from home: If yes, did you have to balance this with taking care of others?
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Not working
Not working: If yes, did you lose your source of income because of COVID-19?
Not working: Why? Check all that apply: Because I am/was sick or under quarantine
Not working: Why? Check all that apply: Because someone in my household was sick or under quarantine
Not working: Why? Check all that apply: Because my place of work was closed and did not offer a remote work option
Not working: Why? Check all that apply: Because I was laid off or lost my employment
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: A change in use of healthcare services
Change in use of healthcare services: If yes, was this an increase or decrease?
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Following media coverage related to COVID-19
Following media coverage related to COVID-19: If yes, on average, how many hours per day did you spend on this?
What are you doing/did you do during the COVID-19 (coronavirus) pandemic? Check all that apply: Changing travel plans
Changing travel plans: If yes, did you travel more or less?
How much is/did COVID-19 impact your day-to-day life?
Notes: 1=Not at all; 2=A little; 3=Much; 4=Very much; 5=Extremely; 6=Decline to answer
